About the Series:
Set in 1956, the series follows WPC 56 Gina Dawson through the trials of being the first female officer 
to serve in her Midlands home town of Brinford. 
Chief Inspector Roger Nelson gives her a small office, previously a closet/storage room, and tasks her 
with making tea, paperwork, dealing with children and women, and told not to distract the men, 
who might seek to protect her in dangerous situations, so they could deal with the important police work. 
She finds she has to work hard to be taken seriously by her male colleagues and is shocked by some of 
the methods employed by Sergeant Sidney Fenton and the blind eye turned by the rest of the officers 
to keep the Chief Inspector in the dark.
The series revolves round two missing boys and a serial attacker and the relationships of the officers families.
